		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />MIDI is really only good for what it's supposed to be - a 'Musical Instrument Digital Interface'.  So if you don't have the exact hardware a song was written for, it always will sound all screwed up.  MIDI really shines in applications like Midines (<a href="http://www.wayfar.net/" class="postlink">http://www.wayfar.net/</a>)

		

		</td>
	</tr>
